results.name: a(1) = 2; a(n+1) is obtained by and trying to change just one digit of a(n), starting with the least significant digit, until a new prime is reached. Take the lexicographically earliest sequence. Digits may be replaced by any nonzero digit.
comment: The sequence is finite with last term a(114) = 149, see link and b-file. - _Reinhard Zumkeller_, Jan 06 2014
link: Reinhard Zumkeller, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..114
